## Routing

Three routes. Configured in `App.tsx`.

```
/                       ŌåÆ HomePage
/configure              ŌåÆ ConfigurePage
/profile/:slug          ŌåÆ ProfilePage
```

`App.tsx` is also where `QueryClientProvider` is mounted. It is 20ŌĆō30 lines at MVP. It does not need to be split into `router.tsx` and `providers.tsx`.

---

## Page Structure

**Page components are thin route wrappers.** `ConfigurePage.tsx` and `ProfilePage.tsx` render the layout wrapper and their primary feature component. They contain no logic.

**`CombinationForm.tsx`** is the only component that owns the full combination selection state (all four inputs). It:
- derives the slicer format from the selected printer
- derives the resolved slug from all four inputs
- controls the generate button state
- delegates navigation on submit

**`availability.ts`** is a module, not a component. It exports `isAvailable(printer, material, nozzle, goal): boolean`. It loads the manifest once and holds it in a module-level cache. It has no UI and no React dependency.

---

## State Ownership

The URL is the single source of truth for the current combination.

| State | Owner | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Form inputs (4 values) | `CombinationForm` local state | Initialized from URL query params on mount |
| Slicer format | Derived from printer in `CombinationForm` | Not shown in the UI at MVP |
| Combination manifest | Module-level cache in `availability.ts` | One fetch per page load; never re-fetched |
| Profile static data (title, highlights, file path) | Fetched from manifest at runtime on Profile page | Served as static JSON from `/combinations.json` |
| Confidence count | Static placeholder at MVP | Stats API deferred post-launch (Cut 2) ŌĆö shows "New profile ŌĆö be the first to report results" |
| `showImportGuide` | `ProfileCard` local state | Set via `DownloadButton` `onDownloadStarted` callback on first download |
| Feedback prompt | Always rendered on Profile page | Visible on page load per S-3.8; not gated by download |
| Feedback outcome | `FeedbackPrompt` local state | Shows confirmation on submit; API wired in M4 |

**There is no global store.** Zustand is not installed and is not used at MVP. If a component needs state, it owns it locally. The conditions for a global store ŌĆö shared UI state across multiple routes, user account state ŌĆö do not exist at MVP.

