## Component Organization

Components inside a page directory are colocated with their page. They are peers of the page component ŌĆö they change together.

```
// Ō£ģ ŌĆö colocated, changed together
src/pages/configure/CombinationForm.tsx
src/pages/configure/PrinterSelector.tsx
src/pages/configure/availability.ts

// ŌØī ŌĆö no features/ directory
src/features/configure/components/CombinationForm.tsx
```

A component moves to `src/shared/` only when it has zero domain knowledge. `SegmentedSelector` receives `options` and `value` ŌĆö it does not know what materials are. `SearchableDropdown` receives an `items` array ŌĆö it does not know what printers are. Domain binding happens in `MaterialSelector.tsx` and `PrinterSelector.tsx`.

If a component is only used in one place and contains product logic, it stays in its page directory. The refactor to shared is cheap when the time comes.

